busybox
=======

busybox provides the userspace utilities (shell, coreutils,
init, mount, etc.) bundled into the runtime VM's rootfs.
synthmodem redistributes a compiled static busybox binary at:

  vm/busybox/busybox

This binary is taken from the Debian bookworm binary package
`busybox-static` (Debian source package `busybox` version
1.35.0-4, i386). It is used only when the slmodemd-pjsip backend
is active (or during the slmodemd-pjsip phase of the auto
backend) and runs inside QEMU; the native backend runs entirely
on the host Node.js runtime and does not invoke it.

Upstream project:  https://busybox.net/
Upstream source:   https://git.busybox.net/busybox/
Debian package:    https://packages.debian.org/bookworm/busybox-static

