Corresponding source
--------------------

GPL-2.0 §3(a) requires that the busybox binary redistributed in
`vm/busybox/` travel with its complete corresponding source.
That obligation is satisfied by committing the upstream Debian
source set to this repository at:

  vm/sources/busybox_1.35.0.orig.tar.bz2
  vm/sources/busybox_1.35.0-4.debian.tar.xz
  vm/sources/busybox_1.35.0-4.dsc

SHA256 sums for all three files are pinned in
`vm/sources/SHA256SUMS`. The top-level `COPYING` enumerates
these paths in its GPL corresponding-source statement.

Modifications from upstream
---------------------------

None. synthmodem redistributes the unmodified Debian binary
package contents. If synthmodem ever ships a patched busybox,
this notice must be updated to record the nature of the
modifications, per GPL-2.0 §2(a).
